Mockito general syntax:

// 1. Mock the dependency
@Mock MyService myService;

// 2. Setup behavior
when(myService.someMethod("input")).thenReturn("output");

// 3. Call the thing youâ€™re testing
String result = classUnderTest.callMyService();

// 4. Verify it did what you expected
assertEquals("output", result);
verify(myService).someMethod("input");

For WebClient:

when(webClient.get()).thenReturn(mockHeadersUriSpec);
when(mockHeadersUriSpec.uri(any())).thenReturn(mockHeadersSpec);
when(mockHeadersSpec.retrieve()).thenReturn(mockResponseSpec);
when(mockResponseSpec.bodyToMono(String.class)).thenReturn(Mono.just("yay"));